unicode name: Latin Small Letter O with Stroke
notes: Redesigned glyph to be distinct from uppercase √ò. This glyph is used by musicutil.lib so I suggest revisiting which of the styles (small, full, superior) we want to use.

Redesigned glyph to sit on baseline rather than extending 1 pixel below. This appears more consistent with text-based music fonts as opposed to scoring-based fonts.

In addition to existing chord names now being uniform in height, script authors may use the extra 1-pixel headroom for superscript  glyphs which can be more compact, horizontally.

I do not see this affecting existing scripts negatively.
